        <abstract>
            
            Included here is everything that was not part of the arrangement work carried out by the Targioni-Tozzetti family, nor however arranged to represent something distinct from Micheli&amp;#39;s collection in the strict sense (thus excluding material that belonged to Micheli but was presumably already treated as separate collections at the time, either by the same author or by others). Here we have the 2 volumes collection of Bryophyta, composed by 978 samples of various species.
        
        </abstract>
